The paper deals with convolutional neural networks applied to spatio-temporal data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves reducing the number of parameters in 3D convolutions, which is also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on datasets, which is a common practice in neural networks (cs.NE) research.
